      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:MNOVH2014">Nakanishi and von Hinüber 2014</ref>. Because it mentions a cornice element, and because the upper pradakṣiṇapatha was only added in Phase III of the stūpa’s construction around 120 CE according to an inscription (<ref target="in:KanA8">KanA8</ref>), this inscription probably dates to around that time.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  <placeName key="pl:Dhānyakaṭaka"><supplied reason="lost">dha</supplied>ñakaḍik<supplied reason="lost">ā</supplied>ya</placeName> aya <persName key="pers:Kan-Dāsī">dāsiyā</persName> sapu<unclear>pha</unclear>gahanika dāna
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>The gift [of a vedikā slab] together with a puphagahani by the venerable <persName key="pers:Kan-Dāsi">Dāsī</persName> from <placeName key="pl:Dhānyakaṭaka">Dhaññakaṭa</placeName>.</p>
      </div>
